page.title: 10Housing in West Wickham (2)
page.content: Chamberlain Crescent: all these houses started as council houses, built in the early 1950's. All are semi-detached. Most have been bought by the occupiers. Cavendish Way: these houses were built in the early 1930's and were owner-oc- cupied from the beginning. They are all semi-detached, but have no garages. Some have coloured leaded lights. Grosvenor Road: many of these houses were built around 1900. They are mostly small. Some of their windows have col- oured leaded lights. Kent Rd and North Rd: all the houses along North Rd and some along Kent Rd were built in the late 1880's. They are very small and have little or no gar- den. These houses are owner-occupied. St David's Close and High Broom Cres.: these houses were built in the 1960's. Some are town houses, others detached. Naomi Britz, Oak Lodge.
